race.comment: POWER OF THE BRAVE (1) has been widely travelled this prep. Failed at Moonee Valley two back then returned to form with a gutsy second over 1000m at Randwick where he led until the final bounds. Very fit and this is a step back in grade. May look to slot in behind a hot tempo this time and will be tough to resist in the closing stages. WALLENDA (4) returns after a 20-week absence. Form in Melbourne last prep was okay but he is more effective on right-handed tracks. Decent fresh performer who is right in this. COOL STORM (9) led and defied all challengers in a BM82 over this trip at Scone recently. Genuine mare who is a definite contender. BE QUIET (13) resumes. Scored with ease at Kembla to kick off last prep. Flying at the trials so keep her very safe first-up with the light weight. REMEMBER JACK (15) has had a seven-week let-up since a real eye-catcher first-up over 1200m at Newcastle. Might still be a run short but shouldn't be undersold.
